<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-702-389  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 702 389.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>EDGE on andamp; about ATandamp;T  Dec 17, 1990 v5 n125 p20(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT EDGE Publishing 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>RBOC merger: U S West telcos to legally merge 1-1-91. (RegionalBell Operating Companies; Mountain Bell, Northwestern Bell,Pacific Northwest Bell)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   U.S. West Communications Group Inc. (Management)Mountain Bell (Acquisitions and mergers)Northwestern Bell Telephone Co. (Acquisitions and mergers)Pacific Northwest Bell Telephone Co. (Acquisitions and mergers).andO;Topic:     Telephone CompaniesMergerLegal IssuesBell Regional Holding CompaniesStrategic Planning.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>All regulatory and bondholder approvals have been secured to legally mergeMountain Bell, Northwestern Bell and Pacific Northwest Bell under thecorporate name U S WEST Communications Inc.andM;The merger will be effective Jan. 1, 1991.andM;U S WEST Inc.'s three telephone companies began operating as U S WESTCommunications in July 1988, but the companies continued to exist as separateentities for legal and regulatory purposes.andP;  With the necessary approvals inplace, the company will now align its legal structure with its operating andmarketing structure.andM;&quot;The merger is a logical extension of the regional marketing and operationalrestructuring that has evolved over the past few years,&quot; said Gary Ames, U SWEST Communications President and Chief Executive Officer.andP;  &quot;Our customersknow us as U S WEST Communications; now everyone we do business with willknow us by the same name.&quot;andM;In addition to the structural advantages, Ames said the merger will bringfuture benefits in the area of debt financing.andP;  The merged company willprovide a basis for strengthened credit quality and stability with its morediversified base.andM;&quot;As the need to raise capital for investments in our telephone networkcontinues, the merged company will be able to issue debt in the mostefficient manner.andP;  That's good for the company and for our customers who willbenefit from network improvements,&quot; he said.andM;Several steps were involved in securing approvals for the merger.andP;  First, thecompany contacted holders of 37 debentures issued by Mountain, Northwesternand Pacific Northwest Bells for approval to modify each indenture to allowthe merger to proceed.andM;U S WEST Communications then reviewed the merger plans with state commissionsin each of the 14 states it serves and made filings in states with laws thatprovide for formal regulatory review of mergers of this type.andM;The company also informed and received approval from the FederalCommunications Commission.andP;  Similarly, U S WEST Communications obtained aPrivate Letter Ruling from the Internal Revenue Service stating that themerger would not constitute a taxable event.andM;U S WEST Communications, the largest subsidiary of U S WEST Inc., serves thecommunications needs of 25 million customers in 14 western states.andM;U S WEST Inc., based in Englewood, Colo., is a $23 billion diversifiedcompany that also owns businesses involved in radio communications, directorypublishing, business communications sales and services, communicationssoftware and financial services.andO;</TEXT></DOC>